The [[Bayer designation]] '''Gamma Caeli''' (γ Cae, γ Caeli) is shared by two [[star system]]s, in the [[constellation]] [[Caelum]]: * [[Gamma¹ Caeli|γ<sup>1</sup> Caeli]] * [[Gamma² Caeli|γ<sup>2</sup> Caeli]] They are separated by 0.22° on the sky.
