==Most isolated major summits==
{{GeoGroup|section=Most isolated major summits}}
Of the most isolated major summits of New Mexico, [[Sierra Blanca (New Mexico)|Sierra Blanca Peak]] exceeds {{convert|200|km|1|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic isolation and three peaks exceed {{convert|100|km|2|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic isolation.
